The paper is primarily focused on parsing expression grammars (PEGs) and their computational power, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also discusses the languages that can be recognized by PEGs, which is related to formal languages (cs.FL). Additionally, the paper introduces a new computational model, the scaffolding automaton, which could be considered a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) or data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of PEGs in terms of their computational power, which could be considered a topic in computational complexity (cs.CC).
